kanban
  backlog[Architecture backlog]
    b1[Define message lifecycle states: Created -> Sent -> Acked -> Synced -> Archived]
    b2[Define replay policy per envelope family: signal, message, file]
    b3[Define observability fields: packetId, transferId, sessionId, peerId, retryCount]

  s1[Sprint 1: Router MVP text path]
    s1a[Implement Router core: transport selection WebRTC-first then Tor fallback]
    s1b[Implement dedup table keyed by packetId + source peer]
    s1c[Implement ACK send/receive state transitions with timeout retry queue]
    s1d[Wire MESSAGE and ACK packet handling end-to-end]
    s1e[Acceptance: offline text delivery works with effectively-once semantics in integration test]

  s2[Sprint 2: Sync + causal ordering]
    s2a[Implement prev_id validation and causal hold queue]
    s2b[Implement gap request protocol and ancestor streaming loop]
    s2c[Implement peer fallback order: own device first then highest uptime peer]
    s2d[Implement PENDING_SYNCS table behavior for offline peers]
    s2e[Acceptance: out-of-order message arrives and is unlocked after gap closure]

  s3[Sprint 3: Persistence + restart safety]
    s3a[Add durable stores for inbox, dedup, retries, sync backlog, peer uptime score]
    s3b[Implement idempotent recovery on app restart for in-flight messages]
    s3c[Implement relay retention and LRU eviction policy hooks]
    s3d[Add migration strategy for protocol state schema versioning]
    s3e[Acceptance: kill-and-restart tests preserve delivery correctness]

  s4[Sprint 4: Crypto foundations]
    s4a[Create shared crypto core: key access, sign/verify, encrypt/decrypt, nonce helpers]
    s4b[Implement protocol-specific protectors: signal protector, tor-message protector, file protector]
    s4c[Replace plaintext signaling protector in production path with signed then encrypted mode]
    s4d[Add replay checks bound to nonce + timestamp windows]
    s4e[Acceptance: tamper, replay, wrong-key tests fail closed]

  s5[Sprint 5: File transfer orchestration]
    s5a[Implement FileEnvelope lifecycle: OFFER CHUNK ACK COMPLETE CANCEL]
    s5b[Implement chunk scheduler with maxInFlightChunks and missing-chunk retransmit]
    s5c[Implement resume from persisted highest contiguous chunk index]
    s5d[Implement transport preference policy TOR vs WEBRTC_DATA vs AUTO]
    s5e[Acceptance: large transfer survives disconnect and resumes correctly]

  s6[Sprint 6: WebRTC resilience + AV]
    s6a[Implement offer retry queues for voice and file with distinct policies]
    s6b[Implement NAT-failure branching with passive wait for file path]
    s6c[Expand AV lifecycle: accept reject control updates teardown]
    s6d[Add reconnect behavior for mid-stream drop cases]
    s6e[Acceptance: retry and fallback behavior matches policy under network churn]

  s7[Sprint 7: Hardening + release readiness]
    s7a[Build full scenario matrix tests: tor-only webrtc-first offline relay restart]
    s7b[Add load and soak tests for 10 to 20 peer target profile]
    s7c[Add structured diagnostics and failure classification for supportability]
    s7d[Finalize protocol compatibility and migration checklist]
    s7e[Acceptance: release candidate passes resilience and recovery gates]

  done[Done criteria]
    d1[Each sprint exits with at least one end-to-end integration test, not only unit tests]
    d2[No sprint closes without explicit rollback and recovery behavior for the new state machine paths]
    d3[Security-sensitive paths include negative tests before feature marked complete]